1)  Main‐Image Analysis and Description

   •  There are actually two separate “mini‐structures” shown.

   LEFT STRUCTURE (6 blocks total, effectively in two layers):
   –  Bottom/Vertical Layer:
      •  Three tall green rectangular prisms standing side by side.  
      •  One orange triangular wedge on the far left (flat face on the floor, apex outward).  
      •  One orange triangular wedge on the far right (flat face on the floor, apex outward).  
   –  Top Layer:
      •  One orange triangular wedge resting horizontally across the tops of the green blocks.
   
   RIGHT STRUCTURE (7 blocks total, in three layers):
   –  Bottom Layer:
      •  Two yellow half‐cylinders, side by side in the front.  
      •  One short green rectangular block behind the left half‐cylinder.  
      •  One blue cube behind the right half‐cylinder.  
   –  Middle Layer:
      •  One long yellow rectangular bar laid horizontally, bridging over the green and blue blocks.  
   –  Top Layer:
      •  One red curved “cradle” block in the center, perched on the yellow bar.  
      •  One red rectangular/cube block to the right of the cradle, at the same height.

2)  Blocks Required from the Dictionary

   LEFT STRUCTURE  
   •  Three copies of block #6 (green vertical rectangular prism).  
   •  One copy of block #16 (orange wedge, apex to the left if placed flat).  
   •  One copy of block #15 (orange wedge, apex to the right if placed flat).  
   •  One copy of block #14 (orange wedge oriented front‐to‐back when placed flat).

   RIGHT STRUCTURE  
   •  Two copies of block #10 (yellow half‐cylinder).  
   •  One copy of block #5 (short green rectangular block).  
   •  One copy of block #2 (blue cube).  
   •  One copy of block #8 (yellow rectangular bar).  
   •  One copy of block #1 (red curved cradle).  
   •  One copy of block #4 (red rectangular/cube block).

3)  Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order

{
  Step1:  Move block with index 6  
  Step2:  Move block with index 6  
  Step3:  Move block with index 6  
  Step4:  Move block with index 16  
  Step5:  Move block with index 15  
  Step6:  Move block with index 14  
  Step7:  Move block with index 10  
  Step8:  Move block with index 10  
  Step9:  Move block with index 5  
  Step10: Move block with index 2  
  Step11: Move block with index 8  
  Step12: Move block with index 1  
  Step13: Move block with index 4  
}
